Wash and dry produce. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{3%cloves}.

Cut @tomato{1} into 1/4-inch-thick wedges.

Have, peel, and thinly slice half the @onion{1}; finely dice remaining onion.

Core, deseed, and dice @long green pepper{1} into 1/4-inch pieces.

== Rice ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{10%tsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat.

Add 1 tsp garlic (2 tsp for 4 servings) and cook, stirring, until fragrant,
~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and 1/2 tsp @salt{1/2%tsp} (1 1/2
cups water and 1 tsp salt for 4). Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a
low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Tomato Salad ==

While rice cooks, in a #medium bowl{}, combine tomato, sliced onion,
@white wine vinegar{5%tsp}, 1/2 tsp sugar, 1/4 tsp salt, and pepper (1 tsp sugar
and 1/2 tsp salt for 4 servings). Set aside, stirring occasionally, until ready
to serve.

== Black Beans ==

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a second small pot over medium-high heat.

Add green pepper, diced onion, @Loisa sazón organic seasoning{1}, 1/2 tsp salt,
and pepper (2 tsp Loisa Organic Sazón Seasoning and 1 tsp salt for 4 servings).

Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are browned and slightly tender,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in @black beans{1} and their liquid and 1/4 tsp sugar (1/2 tsp for 4). Cook,
stirring occasionally, until warmed through and slightly reduced,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired. Keep covered off heat until
ready to serve.

== Pork Chops ==

While beans cook, pat @pork chops{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all
over with remaining Loisa Organic Sazón Seasoning, a pinch of @salt{}, and
@pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork and
cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> If the pork begins to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

Transfer to a #cutting board{} and let rest for at least ~{5%minutes}.

== Garlic Oil ==

Meanwhile, in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine remaining garlic,
2 TBSP oil, and 1/4 tsp salt (4 TBSP oil and 1/2 tsp salt for 4 servings). Cover
tightly with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{60%seconds}. Carefully uncover
and stir.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide rice, beans, and tomato salad (draining first) between plates in
separate sections. Top rice with pork and drizzle with garlic oil. Serve.

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.